\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΝΤΩΜΠΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]Κ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>ΑΣΤΟΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΜΙΥΠΟΚΑΚ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΣΟΡΟΦΑΝΕΔ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al7-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΚΛΕΠΤΟΣΑΝΕ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al8-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">8\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΑΣ&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of Manganaro 1999\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Manganaro suggests this is a decree of Akrai, published in villages in the city's territory. He speculates that the text makes reference to a theft, and perhaps involving a sacred building or sanctuary (line 6: ε]ἰς ὀροφὰν ΕΔ[--; and line 7: ἐ]κλέπτοσαν Ε[--). The text is notable as a rare example of an early Hellenistic document.\u003C/p>  \